            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The runtimepath is unrelated to installation process. The runtimepath is partially based on `XDG_DATA_DIRS`, `XDG_CONFIG_DIRS` and who knows what else which are all variables that can be changed during runtime. I think it's best to just treat `--clean` as \"nvim without user configuration\".\n\nI think trying to determine if an installation is \"local\" or \"global\" and adjust runtimepath based on that is doomed to fail, I simply don't see it turning out well for us.",
