            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "It doesn't matter for me to normal use. I thought rather about bug reports possibly affected by (maybe forgotten) system-wide plugins non-interactively loaded at the start. It's probably very rare case, but still possible. \n\nIt's also not the case caught in my environment. I installed `neovim-runtime` Debian package for the needs of this issue and see built-in plugins under `/usr/share/nvim/runtime`, not contained in the above list. I didn't check how it looks like in other distributions. ",
